&gt; not be as deceptive as we had feared, and therefore methods to
&gt; overcome that deceptiveness (e.g. speciation) may not be entirely
&gt; necessary. Speciation is about searching in multiple regions on the
&gt; basis that some of those regions will get you stuck if you just follow
&gt; the gradient (to a local minima).
&gt;
&gt; In less deceptive fitness landscapes you can start from anywhere and
&gt; follow the gradient to the global maximum (or good enough), so you may
&gt; no longer need multiple species and thus a distance metric either.
&gt;
&gt; Colin
